FY 2026 Plans: The FY 2026 funding supports the following key development activities:
Multi-Waveform Networking and Communications (MWNC): Develop and demonstrate the MWNC systems.
Funding will support the development of an intelligent and autonomous networking gateway that can dynamically
manage and route data across multiple available communication paths, including both Line-of-Sight (LOS) and
Beyond-Line-of-Sight (BLOS) waveforms.

Aviation Wide-Area Network Development: Support architecture design and interoperability, gateway
development, network management, and integration testing as part of the necessary systems engineering,
architecture design, and technology development to enable MH-60 to contribute to enterprise-level information
backbone for BLOS Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (pLEO). Current aviation platforms operate across a collection
of disparate and often stove-piped tactical data links, which limits interoperability and hinders the ability to share
data seamlessly across the joint force. This lack of a unified network fabric is a significant barrier to achieving the
objectives of Distributed Maritime Operations (DMO) and Joint All-Domain Command and Control (JADC2).

Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (pLEO) Emergent Solution: Rapid identification, evaluation, and integration of
emerging commercial pLEO satellite communication (SATCOM) services. This initiative seeks to build resilience
into the Beyond-Line-of-Sight (BLOS) communication architecture by leveraging the explosive growth of the
commercial pLEO market. The objective is to capitalize on commercial innovation, providing the warfighter with a
diverse and resilient portfolio of BLOS communication options.
