       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2027 funding request increased by a total of $24.245M since the President's Budget. $36.023M was added to fund MH-60 Service Life Modernization
       (SLM) efforts. $11.778M was reduced to reflect the realignment of funds for higher Navy priority requirements.

       Schedule:
       1707: Multi-functional Information Distribution System Joint Tactical Radio System (MIDS JTRS) development and integration T&E end date extended from
       4QFY26 to 4QFY28 to resolve priority 1 software deficiencies. Minotaur/Enhanced data Correlation end date extended from 4QFY28 to 4QFY29 for hardware
       ECP release. System Configurations 26/28/30 extended from 4QFY30 to 4QFY31 to continue development of SC32. Air Vehicle DMSMS solution development
       extended from 4QFY30 to 4QFY31 to account for full development of an Automatic Flight Control Computer (AFCC) replacement due to obsolete components.
       Extending System Configuration DT T&E line from 4QFY30 to 4QFY31 to account for biannual SC release schedule to cover SC32 efforts. Radar Tech Refresh

