D. Acquisition Strategy
IFPC-HPM will utilize streamlined acquisition methods, processes and techniques to rapidly prototype the capability. The RCCTO awarded a Prototype Other
Transaction Agreement (pOTA) which delivered four (4) Generation 1 prototype systems in FY 2024 and will deliver up to two (2) Generation 2 HPM rapid prototypes
to soldiers in FY 2026. Continuous soldier integration events will be conducted to provide feedback in support of Army requirements generation, prototype maturation,
fielding residual combat capability to a unit of action, and potential future capability development.




