 3. In FY 2026, FASIT will incrementally fund the separate Small Business Innovative Research Phase III contracts for the development of the Combat Identification
 (Multispectral Targets).

 4. In FY 2027, FASIT will incrementally fund the Small Business Innovative Research Phase III contract for the development of the Combat Identification (Multispectral
 Targets) and Integrated Tactical Vehicle Recorder (ITVR) efforts.

 5. In FY 2026-2031, Instrumentable-Multiple Integrated Laser Engagement System (I-MILES) will leverage the Bridge to Enduring STE TESS Multiple Award Contract
 (BEST MAC) and competitive Other Transactional Authority (OTA) approach to address end-of-useful-life (EUL) and relevancy challenges, as product lines reach critical
 life cycle trigger points. Additionally, the I-MILES program will begin transitioning to sustainment to ensure long-term operational readiness and supportability.

 6. UAS Swarm will continue to provide the U.S. Army Combined Training Centers with UAS Swarm support utilizing the existing Aviation and Missile Technology
 Consortium OTA.

 7. In FY 2024-2025 OMVR awarded an Other Transaction Agreement (OTA) for the design, development, testing, delivery and sustainment of OMVR threat vehicle
 visual modifications (VISMODs) for implementation by the threat force at the CTCs.

 8. In FY 2026, OMVR will incrementally fund initial prototyping of VISMOD threat vehicle variant designs for the Infantry Fighting Vehicle (IFV) and Main Battle Tank
 (MBT). The IFV and MBT represents the greatest large scale combat operational threat representation gap at the CTCs.

 9. In FY27, OMVR will accelerate IFV/MBT vehicle prototype development and add critical supporting threat vehicle design/development to realistically represent threat
 formations across the depth and breadth of the CTC battle space.

