INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604807A$$, 2027, $$This Program Element enhances the advanced development efforts is to address emerging requirements and capabilities for deployable medical equipment and sets.
These efforts focus on transitioning mature technologies into operational systems that enhance medical readiness and support Large-Scale Combat Operations (LSCO).
By leveraging advanced development funding, the Army aims to integrate innovative solutions, improve system performance, and ensure deployable medical capabilities
meet the evolving needs of the force. This includes the refinement, testing, and fielding of medical equipment and sets that provide life-saving care in austere and high-
intensity environments.

 Projects in this PE include the following:

 Project 832 funds the engineering and manufacturing development of medical products for enhanced combat casualty care and follow-on care, including rehabilitation.
 Mature COTS medical products are also evaluated for military use. Consideration will also be given to reduce the medical sustainment footprint through smaller weight
 and cube volume, or equipment independence from supporting materiel. Products from this project will normally transition to OPA Funds.$$, $$Program Elements efforts focus on addressing emerging requirements and capabilities for deployable medical equipment and sets. These initiatives aim to transition
mature technologies into operational systems that enhance medical readiness and support the Army's ability to conduct Large-Scale Combat Operations (LSCO).
Through advanced development funding, the Army integrates innovative solutions, refines system performance, and ensures deployable medical capabilities are
optimized to meet the evolving needs of the force. This includes the development, testing, and fielding of medical equipment and sets designed to deliver life-saving care
in austere and high-intensity operational environments.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025           FY 2026        FY 2027
Title: Field Medical Systems Engineering Development - Medical Readiness                                                                      6.955             6.252          9.744
Description: Funding is provided for engineering and manufacturing development of medical products for diagnostic devices and
testing of medical devices for use in the field.

FY 2026 Plans:
Medical Device Prototype and Testing: Deliver rapid prototype design, fabrication, evaluation, testing, and iterative improvements
for medical devices, support products, components, and systems. Additionally, we will adapt and harden commercial products for
deployment in field environments to sustain and support the Warfighter. Our efforts will include conducting Developmental Test
and Evaluation (DT&E) in compliance with Army and DoW regulations, encompassing Environmental Testing in accordance with
MIL-STD-810G, Performance Verification Testing, and Competitive Analysis. By delivering rapid prototypes, adapting commercial
products, and conducting thorough testing and evaluation, we provide medical devices and systems that are robust, reliable, and
mission-ready. These efforts directly contribute to sustaining and supporting the Warfighter, enhancing operational readiness, and
improving health outcomes in the field. Our commitment to innovation, quality, and compliance ensures that every solution we
deliver is optimized for the unique challenges faced by military personnel in deployment environments.

Medical Field Systems Advanced Development (MFS AD): Continue to advance system integration, experimentation, and testing
of medical devices in support of mobile medical platforms and shelters.
Perform air worthiness certification and evaluation for both developmental and commercial carry-on medical equipment destined
for use aboard Army aircraft required by AR 70-62, for Medical Equipment Sets. Conduct advanced development and initial testing

                                                                                 iological Defense Equipment - Eng Dev             Development

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025       FY 2026         FY 2027
activities in support of reconfigured medical sets with predictive logistical capabilities, medical sensor system networking and
development, and additional medical, dental, and veterinary capabilities.
FY 2027 Plans:
Medical Device Prototype and Testing: Will provide rapid prototype design; fabrication; evaluation and testing; and fixes for
medical devices and medical support products, components and systems as well as harden commercial products for use in a
field environment used to sustain and support the Warfighter. Conduct Developmental Test and Evaluation (DT&E) as required
by Army and DoW regulations, consisting of Environmental T&E IAW Mil-STD-810G; Performance Verification Testing; and
Competitive Analysis.

Medical Field Systems Advanced Development (MFS AD): Continue to drive progress in system integration, experimentation, and
testing of medical devices to enhance the capabilities of mobile medical platforms and shelters. This effort focuses on ensuring
seamless functionality, reliability, and adaptability of medical technologies in dynamic operational environments. This includes
conducting advanced development and initial testing activities to support the reconfiguration of medical sets. These reconfigured
sets will incorporate predictive logistical capabilities, enabling more efficient resource management and supply chain optimization.
Additionally, we will focus on the networking and development of medical sensor systems to facilitate real-time data collection,
monitoring, and decision-making. PM plans to expand the scope of mobile medical platforms by integrating additional capabilities
in medical, dental, and veterinary care. These enhancements will ensure comprehensive support for the health and readiness of
personnel and animals critical to mission success. Through these efforts, we are committed to delivering innovative solutions that
strengthen mobile medical platforms, improve operational efficiency, and provide advanced care in austere and rapidly changing
environments.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding increase to support the modernization of the medical mobile shelter that will support the Warfighter within a deployable
hospital center across all platforms during Large Scale Combat Operations and other scenarios encountered by US Forces.
