D. Acquisition Strategy
The ALPS program was started as an urgent capability in response to multiple Combatant Commands (COCOM) identified operational needs.

An Acquisition Shaping Panel was held 20 May 2024. The Acquisition Decision Memorandum signed 25 Sep 2024 by the Army Acquisition Executive directed the
program to a Major Capability Acquisition pathway and Milestone Decision Authority delegated to PEO Missiles and Space as an ACAT III program. The Material
Development Decision was received Jun 2025 to initiate the program with MS B completed in 1QFY26.

A competitive down selection to a single vendor was completed on 7 Jul 2025. A competitive Other Transaction Authority (OTA) will be awarded for ALPS Mobile in
2QFY26, enabling prototyping and the Engineering, Manufacturing, and Development (EMD) phase of the program.




