A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Counterintelligence (CI) / Human Intelligence (HUMINT) Equipment Program - Army (CIHEP-A) provides CI and HUMINT collectors a full set of expeditionary
capabilities. CIHEP-A will be a scalable and modular equipping program. CIHEP-A capabilities detect and mitigate insider threats, enables military source operations
(MSO), and supports interrogations and debriefing operations to identify and counter adversary intelligence efforts. CIHEP-A kits will provide the collection capability to
CI and HUMINT teams to identify and counter adversary threats.

CIHEP-A is a direct replacement to Counterintelligence (CI) / Human Intelligence (HUMINT) Automated Reporting and Collection Systems (CHARCS) which reaches
End of Useful Life (EUL) FY27.

CIHEP-A will primarily consist of Commercial Off-the-Shelf (COTS) / Government off-the-Shelf (GOTS) components.

