 PrSM Increment 2:
 In November 2022, the Army Acquisition Executive (AAE) determined that the Increment 2 program will follow the major capability acquisition (MCA) pathway. Given
 the technology readiness level (TRL) at the time of transition from science and technology (S&T) to the PrSM Increment 2 program, the earliest EOC deliveries would
 occur is FY 2029. PrSM Increment 2 prototype flight testing begins in 2QFY 2026. A materiel development decision (MDD) occurred on 28 August 2023 and allowed
 the program to enter the materiel solution analysis (MSA) phase. On 25 Feb 2025, the MSA phase was extended until milestone B. PrSM Increment 2 is scheduled
 for a milestone B decision for 4QFY 2026. During the milestone B review, the program will determine an acquisition pathway to support production, delivery, and
 fielding of EOC missiles prior to milestone C. Prototype flight tests planned in FY 2026 will inform milestone B and a production/procurement decision in 3QFY 2026 for
 procurement of long-lead subsystems and components for the first 10 missiles.




