C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Assured Satellite TT&C and Data Services                                                                                             -        0.000        92.537
Description: To streamline efforts within this program element, the Assured Satellite TT&C and Data Services mission thrust
consolidates funds previously captured under 'Satellite Operations Transmit and Receive', 'Satellite C2 Augmentation Services',
and 'Enterprise Systems Engineering and Integration.' This is not a new start.


Assured Satellite TT&C and Data Services provides comprehensive Data Transmit and Receive Network (DTRN) solutions
to enable assured satellite C2 operations for the enterprise, across benign, contested, degraded, and operationally-denied
environments. Modernizes and automates scheduling and resource management, develops new services , integrates cyber
enhancements, and increases resiliency. Provides additional Government and commercial capacity to reduce congestion on
existing networks, address launch projections and growing operational contact demands, and reduce operational risk through
diversified DTRN offerings. Facilitates antenna integration, to include antenna modification or development, when necessary, to
meet mission demands. Integrates capabilities across the DTRN and supports mission operations.

FY 2026 Plans:
The efforts described in the description are funded in the 'Satellite Operations Transmit and Receive', 'Satellite C2 Augmentation
Services', and 'Enterprise Systems Engineering and Integration' major thrusts within this program element in FY 2026, and will
transfer to 'Assured Satellite TT&C and Data Services' in FY 2027.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue the incremental modernization of capabilities supporting the Data Transmit and Receive Network (DTRN) to meet
current and future demand, address user priorities, close capability gaps, and responsively support mission needs. Focus on
expanding contact capacity via modern, automated solutions for Government and commercial antenna network access. Continue
collaborative Enterprise Resource Manager (ERM), Joint Antenna Marketplace (JAM), and Antenna Development efforts, to
include automated scheduling and deconfliction and cross-domain solutioning. Complete the initial JAM prototype efforts and


