Description: The Weapons activity focuses on a number of fundamental scientific areas aimed at expanding the
underlying understanding of disciplines that are broadly useful for a wide range of naval weapon applications,
including undersea weaponry; air weaponry; energetic materials and solid rocket propulsion; both laser and high
power microwave directed energy systems; counter directed energy phenomena; and hypersonic aerodynamics
and materials to address the unique challenges of extreme temperatures and air flow.

