Title: FLRAA MEDEVAC Development and Integration                                                                                             -      25.300         23.100
Description: The FLRAA Medical Evacuation (MEDEVAC) program involves designing, developing, integrating, delivering,
and supporting MEDEVAC mission equipment for the FLRAA. This includes designing platform provisions to facilitate the
rapid installation of the MEDEVAC Mission Equipment Package (MEP). The MEP comprises a sensor capable of visually
acquiring casualties when vision is obscured, and a modular, adjustable, and reconfigurable Patient Handling System (PHS)
with supplemental cabin temperature control if necessary. The aim is to create a MEDEVAC aircraft capable of quickly reaching,
evacuating, and providing enroute critical care to patients on the future battlefield.

